Singing back and forth with another individual who was farther away in another reed patch. In the second half you can easily hear the bird moving around in the reeds as it was only about 10ft away from me. Unfortunately once it got really close to me it only sang a few times. Still, overall quality is good but unfortunately plagued by a plane and some traffic noise.

mediaNotes: Natural song at 12:47pm. Highpass filter 250 Hz in Ocen Audio.

Marsh Wren singing from reeds at the edge of a salt marsh.  I followed the bird around for some time, grabbing recordings whenever possible.  At one point, the bird flew across the trail while singing in flight.  Normalized to -3 dB except for voice announcement at -10 dB. 24-bit/48 kHz WAV file edited with Ocenaudio. Unfiltered.
Natural song from seen bird at 10:59am. 2nd and 3rd cuts best. Highpass filter 250 Hz. Different individual from ML111582671.
